14:31.905 --> 14:35.542
She's so progressive.

14:35.542 --> 14:36.676
I like her.

14:36.676 --> 14:38.045
- Can you believe that bland

14:38.045 --> 14:40.647
and lovely brow conceived
of Frankenstein?

14:40.647 --> 14:43.083
- Such an audience
needs something stronger

14:43.083 --> 14:45.185
than a pretty little love story.

14:45.185 --> 14:47.520
So why shouldn't I
write of monsters?

14:47.520 --> 14:51.658
- She saw it as a gruesome
story of what it was like

14:51.658 --> 14:55.062
to create a version of
yourself from nothing.

14:55.062 --> 14:57.830
That's her through line, I
think, through Frankenstein,

14:57.830 --> 15:00.133
is she had to create
herself from nothing.

15:00.133 --> 15:02.869
It was like all the
pieces just came together

15:02.869 --> 15:04.972
and she was able to really,
I mean quite literally,

15:04.972 --> 15:06.473
all the pieces came together

15:06.473 --> 15:09.209
and she was able to
make this masterpiece.

15:09.209 --> 15:11.878
(ominous music)

15:15.748 --> 15:18.651
- You wake foul dreams
